00:12:29.431 --> 00:12:31.930
wonderful talks about it.You
can go back and read the paper,

00:12:31.930 --> 00:12:35.290
but this probably means in
the atom number in the cavity,

00:12:35.290 --> 00:12:38.070
and the algorithm they have
used to analyze the data

00:12:38.070 --> 00:12:41.660
says that here the photon
number was 0, jumped to 1,

00:12:41.660 --> 00:12:43.500
and jumped back again.

00:12:43.500 --> 00:12:46.320
So you-- If you see
here, for instance,

00:12:46.320 --> 00:12:48.310
there is some overlap,
but you would still

00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:51.320
say, since either there is
