00:33:09.310 --> 00:33:11.400
is completely localized.

00:33:11.400 --> 00:33:14.310
Your Bose-Einstein condensate
if you want in this box,

00:33:14.310 --> 00:33:16.980
or let's just assume one
atom to be more precise,

00:33:16.980 --> 00:33:19.860
and it's completely delocalized.

00:33:19.860 --> 00:33:25.130
But now you focus a laser
beam into the system.

00:33:25.130 --> 00:33:28.180
And the laser beam
would ionize your atom,

00:33:28.180 --> 00:33:31.630
and you could count the
ion with 100% probability.

00:33:31.630 --> 00:33:35.150
And for a short moment,
you flash on the laser

00:33:35.150 --> 00:33:42.210
and the result is
yes, you count.

00:33:42.210 --> 00:33:44.490
You get a count.

00:33:44.490 --> 00:33:47.340
In that moment you
would say my wave

00:33:47.340 --> 00:33:50.240
