00:34:09.030 --> 00:34:14.710
However, if you don't
observe anything,

00:34:14.710 --> 00:34:17.820
you would say, well
now it's actually

00:34:17.820 --> 00:34:20.670
more probable that
the atom is outside.

00:34:20.670 --> 00:34:23.600
Because if it had been
in the laser beam,

00:34:23.600 --> 00:34:26.670
with a certain probability, I
would have detected a photon.

00:34:26.670 --> 00:34:28.730
But the non-detection
of a photon

00:34:28.730 --> 00:34:31.090
means that I revise my estimate.

00:34:31.090 --> 00:34:33.000
And I say it's
much more probable

00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:34.625
that the atom is
outside the laser beam

00:34:34.625 --> 00:34:36.300
than inside the laser beam.

00:34:36.300 --> 00:34:42.130
So this here is exactly how a
non-observation of anything,

00:34:42.130 --> 00:34:46.530
a 0 measurement, modifies
your wave function.

00:34:46.530 --> 00:34:49.340
And the formalism
to incorporate that

00:34:49.340 --> 00:34:53.250
